And he began speaking.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
I am evil.<br>
<br>
Evil? What is evil?<br>
<br>
Never have I seen the combined force of Rallos Zek, Cazic Thule, Innoruuk, Lanys, and The Plaugebringer summed up in one single word.<br>
Evil. It is the force that pawns all of those forementioned gods, it controls their hearts and owns their desires, for it is above them, and it controls them, this forse only known as 'Evil'.<br>
Hate, Death, Decay, Fear, War, Malice. Are they not deemed 'Evil Deeds, Evil Feelings, Evil things?'<br>
These among other things make up this force, which is deemed 'Evil'.<br>
Along side Evil, their is another force.<br>
Mithanel Marr, E. Marr, Tunare, Quellos, Rodcet Nife<br>
This force, is 'Good'.<br>
Love, Peace, Nature, Life, And Valor.<br>
Things that are Good. Feelings that are good, no?<br>
Just like evil, Good is the force that controls those forementioned beings.<br>
Naturally, Evil Fights Good.<br>
For it is the Nature of Evil and Good to do battle.<br>
Like Light and Dark. <br>
All of that, is pretty straight foward. Untill at least, you toss in the third faction.<br>
<br>
Who is to call Good, 'Good'?<br>
Who is to call Evil, 'Evil'?<br>
<br>
The meaningless beings that make up the population of Indifference.<br>
Neutrality some call it.<br>
These beings are neither Good nor Evil. They live for only one thing.<br>
Preservation of Self. They cannot even begin to understand the great conflict between Good and Evil.<br>
They are the untainted and unconverted wildcard. They are 'Common Man'.<br>
They see evil, thus they call it, evil.<br>
They see good, thus they deem it good.<br>
<br>
But why do they call evil, evil?<br>
Because Evil kills their Mothers.<br>
Evil kills their Fathers.<br>
Evil Kills their sons, daughters, and grandchildren.<br>
Evil causes them grief, thus, evil must be bad.<br>
And what is Bad, is evil.<br>
<br>
Why do they call good, good?<br>
Because Good heals their wounds.<br>
It gives them bread. It schools their Children.<br>
It comforts them with Song, it bonds them together in love.<br>
It helps and assists them in any way it can.<br>
All in the Nature of Good.<br>
Good causes them happyness, thus, Good must be nice.<br>
And what is nice, is good.<br>
<br>
Neutrality then sets out on its course of life, living for whatever worthless existance it leads, Good helping it survive, and evil killing it at every turn. Naturally Good defends Neutrality, Thus, Evil and Good Fight.<br>
Without this Assistance from Good, Neutrality could never survive.<br>
So Neutrality is a Leech. A Leech onto Good, using them for their kindness to gain for themselves.<br>
<br>
So, what seperates Neutrality from Good then?<br>
Neutrality has no Moral Sprit.<br>
<br>
If Neutrality sees Evil, it will try to use them.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hey, do you need a Druid to heal your wounds? How about a Barbarian Shaman to assist you? A Gnome Enchantress, a Halfling Rogue.&quot;<br>
<br>
Neutrality feasts on the Arogance of Evil, just as it feasts on the Kindness of Good.<br>
<br>
Evil, Arogant? Yes, of course.<br>
<br>
How many times have you said..<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm just using this Druid lolz&quot;<br>
&quot;This Shaman is just mah bich rofllolz&quot;<br>
<br>
Let me open you into the Mind of Neutrality. <br>
What do you think the Neutrals think of you?<br>
<br>
&quot;Look at this Inkie bastard. Fighting for me. Getting beat around, for me. Taking the hits from monsters and allowing me to gain in training and maybe some pieces of armor if I allow him to continue. All I have to do is cast my Silly Sprit of Wolf spell and heal him every now and again, and he's my pet.&quot;<br>
<br>
Nice going, Jobarn. You really showed that Druid who's boss, huh? And it even works the other way around.<br>
<br>
That same Human Warrior, that believes in nothing is simply saying.<br>
<br>
&quot;Look at this Inkie Priest Bastard. Healing me. Blasting for me. Protecting me. I gain in Training, and I get to have some fun! Even gain some loot for myself, while this stupid Inkie thinks he's running the Show.&quot;<br>
<br>
Good work, he's really on a short leash.<br>
<br>
Thats why I do not group with Neutrals. I'm not the one to be used by them, nor will I assist them in training.<br>
<br>
I kill Neutrals. Why? Because I am Evil.<br>
<br>
And who deems evil, evil?<br>
The Neutrals. Why? Because We kill them.<br>
<br>
But, you may want to help the Neutrals. By all means, go for it.<br>
<br>
Assist the Neutrals.<br>
And what do the Neutrals deem this?<br>
Good.<br>
<br>
Good.<br>
<br>
Good.<br>
<br>
And what is good? ((Look up there ^))<br>
You poor Darkelf, by helping the Neutrals, you have just tossed aside 'Evil' and become as good as the Paladin you tried to kill yesterday.<br>
<br>
Helping the Neutrals is and will always be 'Good'.<br>
And who deems good, Good? The Neutrals.<br>
Why do they deem good, Good? Because Good helps them.<br>
<br>
I am not Good. I am evil.<br>
<br>
So I kill Neutrals.<br>
<br>
Another thing. I have to say Neutrality, you really have done a job on the forces of 'Evil'. The a Testiment to your success so far is all wrapped up in a Guild called &quot;Fire and Fury&quot; no?<br>
<br>
That ends now. The Darkelves are not for sale anymore. Go get your own damn loot.<br>
<br>
That is all.<br>
