</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukimayasilverbark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kimaya Silverbark</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/11/02 11:47:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=121.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Good, Evil, and the other thing.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Somewhere into the beginning of Shintou's speech, Kimaya stopped playing around in the back of the room.  Halfway through, she even stopped giggling and whispering.  By the end of it, she had stopped smiling.  As Shintou finished his speech, she climbed up to stand on her stool so she could see him clearly over the crowd.  With an uncharacteristic somberness, almost coldness, she turned to address him back.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
And that's how evil defines neutrality.<br>
<br>
Oh yes, Shintou, you are evil.  <br>
<br>
You are quite clearly evil, with all the self-congratulating and angst-absorbed warmth you evil folks wrap around yourselves seeking comfort in the dark and cold world you work to create.  And like other evil folks, you pretend that evil is some great, living force that is powerful enough to exist outside mere gods or mortals.  You wave your evil label like a banner to advertise and even justify your actions, just like all the ruthless warlords, the rampaging armies and heartless merchants that have gone on before you.  <br>
<br>
People like you always say you hurt, maim or kill because you are evil, as though there were some outside force controlling you and you simply have no other recourse.  The fact is that what you call evil is simply the choices you make, and you make those choices for various reasons -- apparently because you are shortsighted, selfish and mean.<br>
<br>
Oh yes, and what about good?  <br>
<br>
Oh, those that run around calling themselves good make the same kind of claims that evil folks do.  They pretend what they do is dictated to them by a higher purpose grander than their own gods themselves, just like you do.  And, like evil, they wave their label like a banner as they do things from handing out bread to the hungry to trying to kill off entire populations they call evil.<br>
<br>
They also pretend they have no choice but to heal people and feed people, just like they say that good requires for them to go out and hurt, maim or kill people.  The fact is that what they call good is simply the choices they make, and they make those choices for various reasons -- they may be generous and giving, or they might just be shortsighted and bigoted.<br>
<br>
And what about neutral?  <br>
<br>
Well, the problem with good and evil defining neutral is that being good and being evil is all about picking sides to justify themselves and define everyone else.  And since you're evil, and all about being selfish, you make the assumption that neutrals are just out there to be selfish too.  <br>
<br>
The fact is that most neutrals don't believe in picking sides, they're too busy trying to make their own choices to try to blame those choices on banners and labels.  Beyond that, there are as many different kinds of neutral as there are wolves in the woods, so I can't define neutrality for you and I won't even try.  But I will tell you what I see about good and evil, and why I think your speech about what neutrals think is a load of gnoll spittle.<br>
<br>
I am a child of Nature.<br>
I am a child of Tunare.<br>
Whether you like it or not, Tunare is still YOUR mother, Shintou.  Even as much as he twisted, the Hateful one couldn't take that away.<br>
Whether you like it or not, Tunare still loves your race, and the race of the trolls, and the race of the humans, all as much as she loves our siblings the wolves and the fay.<br>
Whether you like it or not, it is the gifts of Tunare and the gifts of our grandmother that grow the wheat to bake your bread.  She feeds you and clothes you, as she feeds and clothes us all.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Her voice grows stronger and harsher, a firey glow smouldering in her eyes.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
So when I see good and evil go to attack and kill her children without need for food or safety<br>
When I see wolves dead in the woods with their skin and their meat left to rot in the sun<br>
I think of how the murderers call themselves evil<br>
I think of how the murderers call themselves good<br>
And I fail to see the difference.<br>
<br>
So go, call yourself evil.  Use your label as an excuse to hurt or kill anyone you like.  It doesn't make any difference.  Your choices are your own, and it is you, yourself, who will answer for them when we all return to meet the Nameless.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Kimaya slowly sits back down on her stool.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/unhjstr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NhJstr</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_purplespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/11/02 11:59:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=121.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Good, Evil, and the other thing.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  A pair of eyes glint from underneath the hooded cape.  Those standing around the creature here a slight chuckle. </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
So, things shall begin this way.  With the foolishness of this dark elf.  Will they never understand?  Will they never get that they are all simply pawns?  He thinks that the neutrals use him, while he is being used by this 'evil' that he speaks of.<br>
<br>
And what is this of neutrals knowing not of good and evil, and of having no morals?  Neutral being nothing more than a leech?  What foolishness has he been contaminated by?  A neutral person has morality, they have a reason for existence.  It is not simply for self preservation, it is for preservation of all.  For if either good or evil were to become too powerful, then existence would soon cease to be.  No, neutral is there to keep the balance, to ensure the future.  But, obviously you are too consumed by emotion to reason with logic.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  The figure sighs. </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Soon you will see your foolishness, Shintou.  When your hate and rage brings forth the ultimate beings of evil, the nature of good shall respond.  And then my master will have his prophecy fulfilled.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  The figure leaves the area, heading back to let his master know of what is beginning.  But before he leaves he turns, and the hood falls away, and the face of Id is clearly seen.  Casting one last glance at Shintou, he sees Sarhea out of the corner of his eye, and sees the conviction in her face.  Shaking his head, he returns to his natural form, that of the wolf, and begins the journey to see Trakanon.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p>Id<BR>
The true Menemas<BR>
Starspun <BR>
Firionia Vie <BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukallee.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kallee</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dances with Skeletons</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/11/02 12:31:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=121.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Good, Evil, and the other thing.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Kallee listened intently to the dark elf's speech, knowing that questions of good and evil were ones that had plagued her of late, as she journeyed forth throughout Norrath and encountered races that used such labels.<br>
She pulled her journal from her backpack and began to scribble her thoughts down in a haphazard manner...</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Labels.  He starts a war based on labels.<br>
I am Tier`Dal, like this knight here is...and he calls forth for all to hear he is evil.  He plays to the labels of the Lightwalkers. <br>
I do not see myself as evil.  I had spoken of this the other night...I see myself on the One True Path.  I think...<br>
A Path, nonetheless.  But I can't define it as evil.<br>
Evil to me would be the High Elves, those rebels who disowned us.  Evil would be those Halflings that inhabit the forests about Neriak.  Evil would be those that call me Evil because I am Tier`Dal.<br>
Therefore, perhaps, in a way...Shintou is Evil too...<br>
But I do hold forth his stand on Neutrality.  Ours is not a world that can sustain nor abide the existence of these individuals...agnostic, neutral, or both...those who wish to work both ends against the middle.  They are weak.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Kallee stopped writing suddenly, the ink trailing off the page, as she felt someone may be reading over her shoulder.  She closed the book and dropped it back into her pack, and quickly stood up and left the gathering, trying to slip out before anyone noticed.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
 <p>Kallee<BR>
